post_cb({"bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_22502324_22502324_1": {"length": 47, "quality": 0.9591836734693877, "section_id": 531}}, "n3337": {"so_22502324_22502324_1": {"length": 47, "quality": 0.9591836734693877, "section_id": 522}}, "n4659": {"so_22502324_22502324_1": {"length": 47, "quality": 0.9591836734693877, "section_id": 552}}}, "22502324": {"ViewCount": "163", "Body": "<p>There is a paragraph in the C++03 standard related to preprocessor macro replacement:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_22502324_22502324_0\">16.3.4 Rescanning and further replacement</p>\n<p id=\"so_22502324_22502324_1\">If the name of the macro being replaced is found during this scan of\n  the replacement list (not including the rest of the source file\u2019s\n  preprocessing tokens), it is not replaced. <strong>Further, if any <em>nested\n  replacements</em> encounter the <em>name of the macro being replaced</em>, it is not\n  replaced. These nonreplaced macro name preprocessing tokens are no\n  longer available for further replacement even if they are later\n  (re)examined in contexts in which that macro name preprocessing token\n  would otherwise have been replaced.</strong></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>What do the highlighted sentences mean?  First the standard never defined the term \"<em>nested replacements</em>\". Furthermore, if a nested replacement means the example given below</p>\n<pre><code>#define a b\n#define b c\n#define c d\n#define d a b e\n#define e m\n\na // expanded to \"a b m\"\n</code></pre>\n<p>Which one is the <em>\"name of the macro being replaced</em>\"(note singular noun used) ? Because here <code>a</code> is replaced to <code>b</code> then to <code>c</code> then to <code>d</code> then to <code>a b m</code>, and there are &gt;1 macros being replaced and both <code>a</code> &amp; <code>b</code> are the name of the macros encountered previously. But clearly the standard is not using a plural noun so it should not mean both <code>a</code> and <code>b</code> here.</p>\n<p>Can someone clarify the meaning of this paragraph.</p>\n", "Title": "How to Interpret This Paragraph of the C++ Standard Related to Macro Replacement", "CreationDate": "2014-03-19T10:06:56.737", "LastActivityDate": "2016-07-03T09:03:30.643", "CommentCount": "4", "FavoriteCount": "0", "PostTypeId": "1", "LastEditDate": "2016-07-03T09:03:30.643", "LastEditorUserId": "4370109", "Id": "22502324", "Score": "3", "OwnerUserId": "237575", "Tags": "<c++><c-preprocessor><language-lawyer>", "AnswerCount": "0"}});